        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="370" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Haldeman</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 39.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 31, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Your despatch No. 44, of the 8th instant, has been
                    received, and your graphic account of the late popular tumult in Stockholm,
                    occasioned by the stand taken by Count Manderstrom on the question of the war
                    now raging in Denmark, has been read with much interest.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jacob S. Haldeman</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Stockholm.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
